# EAS Build does NOT respect .gitignore for its upload archive by default — it archives the
# whole working directory (minus node_modules) unless told otherwise here. Confirmed root cause
# of a real build failure: the local android/ folder (gitignored, regenerated locally via
# `expo prebuild` for Android Studio dev) carries a native build cache (android/app/.cxx/) full
# of absolute Windows paths baked in from this machine. Uploaded as-is to EAS's Linux build
# servers, those paths don't exist there, breaking Gradle's autolinking project resolution
# (react-native-worklets was the first to fail, but the same rot affects any autolinked module).
# This is the same class of bug already hit and fixed during the iOS port (§4.6 of the old iOS
# port report): never carry a locally-generated native folder across environments, regenerate
# instead. Excluding /android and /ios here means EAS's own `expo prebuild` always runs fresh,
# server-side, with zero local-machine contamination possible.
/android
/ios

# Same reasoning, smaller scale — local Expo module native build artifacts, already gitignored,
# no reason to ever upload them.
modules/*/android/build/
modules/*/android/.cxx/
modules/*/android/.gradle/
modules/*/ios/build/

# Editor/OS cruft, never needed for a build.
.expo/
.git/
